in england , about 140,000 people suffer a heart attack each year , and a quarter of them suffer yet another seizure or heart attack .
heart attacks and strokes are caused by a build-up of fat that creates a continuous layer on the walls of the arteries .
if this layer is removed , a blood clot can occur , blocking blood access to the heart and the onset of a heart attack .
if the clot is released , the bloodstream can go on , block the blood supply to the brain and cause a stroke .
people who have already had a heart attack are at higher risk of another seizure .
