the new rules are intended to apply to all persons without a thai passport who decide to get a sim from one of the local operators when they stay in thailand .
that is , not only to tourists , but also to people with long-term visas who , for example , have worked or closed marriages in thailand .
the secretary-general of the office of the national broadcasting and telecommunications commission , takorn tantasith , has informed that there will be no exceptions .
a plan to sell sim intended exclusively to foreigners was introduced by the national telecoms regulator in early august .
the new measure , which will allow monitoring of their position , intends to be introduced by the authorities within six months .
according to tantasith , it is a means of maintaining national security that will allow the crime to be dealt with by foreigners .
in addition , the so-called tourist sim is intended to help detect people who exceed the permitted length of stay .
for sellers , a special sim for foreigners should also be found alongside the sim intended exclusively for thais within six months .
the difference will be the monitoring function , which will be permanently switched on for cards intended for persons without a thai passport .
it won &apos;t be possible to turn it off .
&quot; this feature is not in the sim for thais , because we can always track them easily , &quot; tantasith added .
it must be added that in thailand , pre-plaques are not anonymous as in the czech republic .
the seller requires proof of identity .
on the other hand , for several years , one of the operators was handing out free launch sim to tourists at airports .
they were fully anonymous .
ten telecommunications regulators from other asian countries , including malaysia or singapore , are also considering the introduction of the same measure as thailand .
there are currently mandatory sim registrations , but the legal use of the surveillance system is not possible .
however , the forthcoming measure does not imply an obligation for foreigners to acquire a local operator when they enter the country .
they can , of course , use roaming services with their own home sim , in which case the thai authorities will be short on them .
in fact , the operators of that country know only relevant network information when they cross the border , that is to say , after the sim is logged on to their network .
so they know the phone number , but not the information about the owner .
however , the difference in roaming prices compared to those of local operators is so abysmal that even most tourists will start looking for local sim during their stay in thailand .
efforts by the authorities to have oversight of the movement of foreigners have legally received immediate criticism from foreigners living in thailand .
tantasith reassures the situation , and in the context of protecting privacy the upcoming system likens it to the obligation to provide a residential address in immigration documents .
in addition , the police will need a warrant if they need to monitor a particular person .
there will be an unspecified punishment for any abuse of the system .
&quot; if the service provider monitors the location of the sim without a court order , he will be charged with a crime , &quot; tantasith added .
in addition , the system should also maximise the use of prepaid cards .
